HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 944
By Boyd
A RESOLUTION to recognize the nuclear energy industry in the
State of Tennessee.
WHEREAS, the men and women of Tennessee have always answered America's call to
service; and
WHEREAS, Tennessee opened the Atomic Age with Manhattan Project facilities that
brought an end to World War II and ensured global peace for decades to win the Cold War, and
the State continues to perform essential missions today; and
WHEREAS, Oak Ridge National Laboratory is the largest science and energy laboratory
for the U.S. Department of Energy and conducts wide-ranging research to address the nation's
energy, quantum computing, and security challenges to ensure America's future; and
WHEREAS, since 1943, the Y-12 National Security Complex has been a premier
manufacturing complex dedicated to making America and the world a safe place, and it
continues to fuel our nation's naval reactors; and
WHEREAS, United Cleanup Oak Ridge's successful cleanup of the former Manhattan
Project-era K-25 Complex for the Department of Energy and transfer of land back to the local
community has spurred $12 billion in next-generation nuclear investments and a projected
4,000 new jobs in Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, the U.S. Department of Energy's continued investments in enduring national
security, science, and environmental cleanup missions in Tennessee are the anchors of the
nation's first Nuclear Innovation District; and
WHEREAS, Governor Bill Lee's bold vision with the General Assembly to create a
"Nuclear Development Fund" to spur continued nuclear energy and supply-chain investments in
HJR0944
013120
- 1 -

every corner of the Volunteer State has led to the American Nuclear Society naming Tennessee
as "the epicenter" of nuclear innovation and investments; and
WHEREAS, America has called on Tennessee again to lead the way in restoring
American dominance in reliable, advanced energy development investments; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we applaud the continued growth and expansion of the nuclear industry in
the Volunteer State, thank its employees for their exemplary service to the citizens of the State
of Tennessee and the world, and extend our best wishes for their continued success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
